cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it deals with aspect term extraction, which is a task in natural language processing. The use of machine learning algorithms such as BLSTM-CRF and the construction of datasets for ATE also suggest that it could belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the method on human annotated test sets indicates that it could also belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of unsupervised learning techniques and the focus on precision scores suggest that it could belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
